1
00:00:04,005 --> 00:00:07,575
Three years ago,
I was supposed to get married.

2
00:00:08,909 --> 00:00:11,579
But I fell for someone else.

3
00:00:12,146 --> 00:00:13,647
<i>It was him.</i>

4
00:00:14,248 --> 00:00:16,684
<i>He was my student.</i>

5
00:00:18,386 --> 00:00:20,321
I'm the only one still where I was,

6
00:00:21,422 --> 00:00:22,957
unable to move forward.

7
00:00:23,591 --> 00:00:24,558
Let's forget.

8
00:00:25,393 --> 00:00:26,727
I'll help you forget.

9
00:00:28,629 --> 00:00:29,864
You have moved forward.

10
00:00:30,998 --> 00:00:32,299
Ms. Suenaga.

11
00:00:33,200 --> 00:00:34,735
You're moving forward.

12
00:00:36,070 --> 00:00:41,208
Slowly, one step at a time,
you're moving forward.

13
00:00:41,842 --> 00:00:46,981
If you're still hung up on Hijiri,
and just using me…

14
00:00:47,048 --> 00:00:49,917
Treating me like some substitute.

15
00:00:51,919 --> 00:00:52,820
I can't take it.

16
00:01:03,464 --> 00:01:04,365
It's okay.

17
00:01:05,533 --> 00:01:06,534
It's okay.

18
00:01:09,670 --> 00:01:10,504
It's okay.

19
00:01:17,344 --> 00:01:19,113
Ms. Chizuru, your mouth.

20
00:01:19,180 --> 00:01:20,981
Your mouth.

21
00:01:21,048 --> 00:01:22,316
Ah, yeah.

22
00:01:23,084 --> 00:01:27,721
Wait, so you're saying that despite
knowing everything about your past,

23
00:01:27,788 --> 00:01:30,391
Mr. Nogami still hugged you
saying it was okay?

24
00:01:31,725 --> 00:01:34,261
I know I can't take advantage
of his kindness.

25
00:01:35,362 --> 00:01:37,631
But I was relieved.

26
00:01:39,233 --> 00:01:44,505
It made me think that maybe it's
okay for me to stay here.

27
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:48,275
I'm relieved too.

28
00:01:48,342 --> 00:01:52,880
It's been three years since we've talked
about your love life. It's a good match.

29
00:01:52,947 --> 00:01:54,448
No, please.

30
00:01:55,483 --> 00:01:59,286
Mr. Nogami hasn't acted
any differently since then.

31
00:01:59,854 --> 00:02:02,790
We did grab a bite to eat
together once at the next station over.

32
00:02:02,857 --> 00:02:04,658
Then I'll be your matchmaker.

33
00:02:04,725 --> 00:02:05,993
That's okay.

34
00:02:06,060 --> 00:02:07,728
I'm kidding.

35
00:02:07,795 --> 00:02:08,863
Listen, Hijiri.

36
00:02:08,929 --> 00:02:11,599
Your next boyfriend will
probably be the man you marry.

37
00:02:11,665 --> 00:02:15,269
So wish for the best and go for it.
Just ask him out yourself!

38
00:02:15,336 --> 00:02:18,405
Take the lead and ask him out. Hurry!

39
00:02:18,472 --> 00:02:19,740
Don't run. Don't fall.

40
00:02:20,474 --> 00:02:21,942
Good morning.

41
00:02:22,610 --> 00:02:23,444
Ow…

42
00:02:24,445 --> 00:02:25,312
Hey!

43
00:02:34,955 --> 00:02:36,056
Tachibana?

44
00:02:39,260 --> 00:02:41,896
-Tachibana!
-Are you okay?

45
00:02:41,962 --> 00:02:43,597
-You okay?
-Are you okay?

46
00:02:43,664 --> 00:02:45,533
-Is it your stomach?
-Are you alright?

47
00:02:45,599 --> 00:02:48,369
-Nogami, get the school nurse.
-Okay.

48
00:02:49,069 --> 00:02:50,604
Let me grab your bag for you.

49
00:02:51,172 --> 00:02:54,542
<i>-Malnutrition?</i>
<i>-And the resulting anemia.</i>

50
00:02:54,608 --> 00:02:56,744
<i>There are more and more cases.</i>

51
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:59,446
They get enough calories,
but not nutrition.

52
00:02:59,980 --> 00:03:01,048
Where's her mother?

53
00:03:01,115 --> 00:03:03,817
She said she was working all weekend.

54
00:03:03,884 --> 00:03:07,254
No way, I bet she was with a guy.

55
00:03:13,027 --> 00:03:14,094
<i>No answer.</i>

56
00:03:14,161 --> 00:03:15,729
<i>But I left a message.</i>

57
00:03:15,796 --> 00:03:18,699
<i>I heard a rumor she got dumped</i>
<i>and is taking it badly.</i>

58
00:03:18,766 --> 00:03:23,938
There are women like that
who need a man to keep her life stable.

59
00:03:24,505 --> 00:03:25,973
What a mess.

60
00:03:26,507 --> 00:03:29,443
You prioritize your kid, obviously!

61
00:03:29,510 --> 00:03:33,747
Anyway, I'll stay behind
and wait for her mother to pick her up.

62
00:03:33,814 --> 00:03:35,583
-Please do.
-I'll stay with you.

63
00:03:38,819 --> 00:03:40,721
-Thanks.
-No problem.

64
00:03:43,023 --> 00:03:44,191
Excuse me.

65
00:03:44,692 --> 00:03:46,060
What're you reading?

66
00:03:47,328 --> 00:03:48,862
Let me see.

67
00:04:07,581 --> 00:04:09,850
It's been three years now.

68
00:04:09,917 --> 00:04:12,453
<i>I ripped them apart</i>

69
00:04:12,519 --> 00:04:14,688
<i>to get my little boy back.</i>

70
00:04:14,755 --> 00:04:18,092
<i>But now he hates me,</i>
<i>and won't even see me.</i>

71
00:04:18,158 --> 00:04:20,027
If you go, there's no coming back.

72
00:04:22,730 --> 00:04:24,031
I'm back.

73
00:04:24,932 --> 00:04:26,166
You're looking again.

74
00:04:27,001 --> 00:04:30,204
Come on, you need to let this go.

75
00:04:30,271 --> 00:04:32,006
Take deep breaths.

76
00:04:32,072 --> 00:04:34,141
What if Akira finds out about her?

77
00:04:34,208 --> 00:04:35,709
And breathe out.

78
00:04:36,543 --> 00:04:40,614
He's finally settled down,
if he gets dragged back in again,

79
00:04:41,815 --> 00:04:43,684
there's no coming back.

80
00:04:43,751 --> 00:04:46,920
Akira's not going to find out,
I'd never tell him.

81
00:04:46,987 --> 00:04:48,455
I'll go see Ms. Shioya.

82
00:04:48,522 --> 00:04:50,591
From his junior high school?

83
00:04:51,258 --> 00:04:54,295
I'm going to ask if the school
knows about this.

84
00:05:06,573 --> 00:05:10,577
Sorry for the short notice,
and for not contacting you.

85
00:05:11,211 --> 00:05:12,579
I've been working nonstop.

86
00:05:16,216 --> 00:05:18,519
You're working that much?

87
00:05:19,153 --> 00:05:21,455
I don't want my mom paying for me.

88
00:05:23,190 --> 00:05:25,592
What's your job again?

89
00:05:26,493 --> 00:05:27,394
Bread factory.

90
00:05:28,829 --> 00:05:32,433
I brand the bread after
they're done baking.

91
00:05:33,167 --> 00:05:34,001
Brand?

92
00:05:35,502 --> 00:05:36,937
-That's funny.
-Not really.

93
00:05:49,450 --> 00:05:51,585
I want to hold hands.

94
00:06:04,398 --> 00:06:06,367
Sorry about before.

95
00:06:08,235 --> 00:06:10,604
For not going through with it.

96
00:06:11,372 --> 00:06:15,843
You know, I don't think I was ready.

97
00:06:16,877 --> 00:06:20,381
I just went for it,
but I didn't know what you were thinking

98
00:06:21,348 --> 00:06:24,551
or how you felt about me.
I still don't know, so--

99
00:06:25,386 --> 00:06:26,453
What?

100
00:06:31,992 --> 00:06:32,893
Damn.

101
00:06:34,428 --> 00:06:35,262
I like this.

102
00:06:37,364 --> 00:06:38,198
What?

103
00:06:45,873 --> 00:06:47,040
Can I get used to this?

104
00:06:54,248 --> 00:06:57,684
Can we say that we're dating?

105
00:07:01,088 --> 00:07:03,190
DON'T CRY ANYMORE, KURIZURA

106
00:07:06,627 --> 00:07:11,031
<i>If her mother can't come get her,</i>
<i>Ayano can come stay with me.</i>

107
00:07:11,098 --> 00:07:11,965
That'd be great!

108
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:16,136
I'm glad you were here.

109
00:07:16,203 --> 00:07:20,641
Please, if I were alone,
I think I would've just panicked.

110
00:07:20,707 --> 00:07:21,542
It's nothing.

111
00:07:22,176 --> 00:07:24,011
I'm glad you're the head teacher.

112
00:07:24,545 --> 00:07:25,379
Oh, please.

113
00:07:29,216 --> 00:07:30,217
Um.

114
00:07:32,052 --> 00:07:32,886
Um.

115
00:07:35,189 --> 00:07:38,192
Come to think of it, we haven't

116
00:07:39,960 --> 00:07:41,195
talked about it.

117
00:07:42,729 --> 00:07:43,664
If…

118
00:07:47,034 --> 00:07:47,868
If you'd like…

119
00:07:51,104 --> 00:07:52,739
No, now's not the time.

120
00:07:56,410 --> 00:07:59,580
But we don't get to talk much like this.

121
00:08:08,989 --> 00:08:09,823
Um…

122
00:08:15,929 --> 00:08:17,831
I'm sorry I'm late.

123
00:08:19,266 --> 00:08:21,034
I couldn't get out of work.

124
00:08:21,835 --> 00:08:24,071
No one's on the register's now.

125
00:08:24,137 --> 00:08:26,139
I called your work.

126
00:08:29,343 --> 00:08:31,979
The manager said you had
the day off today.

127
00:08:33,013 --> 00:08:36,483
Actually, I wasn't feeling well.

128
00:08:36,550 --> 00:08:38,185
I was resting at home.

129
00:08:38,252 --> 00:08:40,220
I spoke to Mr. Nogami.

130
00:08:41,154 --> 00:08:43,156
If this happens again,

131
00:08:44,691 --> 00:08:45,859
your parents…

132
00:08:47,227 --> 00:08:50,531
-My parents?
-In case something happens to Ayano.

133
00:08:50,597 --> 00:08:52,633
We could have her grandparents--

134
00:08:52,699 --> 00:08:53,634
Please stop.

135
00:08:55,102 --> 00:08:57,404
I've cut ties with my parents.

136
00:08:58,372 --> 00:09:01,108
I'm only staying in their home,
but that's all.

137
00:09:01,174 --> 00:09:02,276
We're no contact.

138
00:09:04,945 --> 00:09:08,115
Did you call them already?

139
00:09:09,216 --> 00:09:11,351
No, not yet.

140
00:09:13,921 --> 00:09:15,956
-But if--
-If you overstep…

141
00:09:17,157 --> 00:09:18,692
I'll reveal your secret.

142
00:09:24,264 --> 00:09:28,869
You have a secret, don't you?

143
00:09:37,945 --> 00:09:40,681
I don't know what you're talking about.

144
00:09:40,747 --> 00:09:43,784
I know about it.

145
00:09:49,823 --> 00:09:50,757
Mom!

146
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:54,928
Ayano, I'm sorry I'm late!

147
00:09:56,330 --> 00:09:57,331
Here.

148
00:09:59,900 --> 00:10:00,767
Clip.

149
00:10:03,437 --> 00:10:06,106
Ms. Tachibana, you had me worried.

150
00:10:06,173 --> 00:10:08,475
-I'm sorry, Mr. Nogami.
-We're fine.

151
00:10:09,476 --> 00:10:13,013
But I think your daughter was missing you.

152
00:10:14,481 --> 00:10:17,050
Considering her health as well.

153
00:10:19,953 --> 00:10:22,489
Perhaps you should rely on your parents--

154
00:10:22,556 --> 00:10:26,293
No, I promise not to cause
any worry again.

155
00:10:27,227 --> 00:10:29,930
-Just please don't involve them.
-But--

156
00:10:29,997 --> 00:10:33,000
If you involve them,
they'll take Ayano from me.

157
00:10:35,636 --> 00:10:39,373
I may not be a good mother,
but I love Ayano.

158
00:10:40,774 --> 00:10:42,776
You understand, don't you?

159
00:10:45,245 --> 00:10:46,446
Ms. Suenaga?

160
00:10:55,889 --> 00:10:57,524
I'm sure Ayano is tired,

161
00:10:59,459 --> 00:11:01,228
so I think it's best

162
00:11:02,262 --> 00:11:04,631
if she took her home for today.

163
00:11:10,804 --> 00:11:11,838
Okay.

164
00:11:12,839 --> 00:11:15,676
But if something happens again,

165
00:11:16,576 --> 00:11:18,278
I will be contacting your parents.

166
00:11:19,946 --> 00:11:21,348
Let's go, Ayano.

167
00:11:58,604 --> 00:11:59,972
-Thanks, Akira.
-Sure.

168
00:12:00,840 --> 00:12:02,675
-I'm off then.
-Have a good day.

169
00:12:04,010 --> 00:12:04,810
Kokonoe.

170
00:12:04,877 --> 00:12:06,746
-Yo.
-Long time, cadet.

171
00:12:06,812 --> 00:12:10,349
Like I said, Mr. Joffe,
this is just my hairstyle.

172
00:12:10,416 --> 00:12:11,851
What's up?

173
00:12:13,261 --> 00:12:14,962
-Iwasaki?
-Yeah.

174
00:12:16,197 --> 00:12:18,299
We're going out, why do you ask?

175
00:12:21,369 --> 00:12:23,704
What, you came all this way to ask me?

176
00:12:26,574 --> 00:12:27,708
Do you like Iwasaki?

177
00:12:29,677 --> 00:12:30,378
I do.

178
00:12:30,445 --> 00:12:33,648
We're not kids anymore,
there's different levels of like.

179
00:12:35,349 --> 00:12:37,218
What kind of like is it?

180
00:12:43,724 --> 00:12:46,994
I don't have to see
the scary part of myself.

181
00:13:00,541 --> 00:13:01,509
Why now?

182
00:13:01,576 --> 00:13:04,011
Kuroiwa's mom found this.

183
00:13:05,346 --> 00:13:06,047
Really?

184
00:13:06,113 --> 00:13:11,285
Ebihara's little brother happened
to see her talking to the teachers.

185
00:13:11,352 --> 00:13:13,588
-Did you tell Kuroiwa?
-No.

186
00:13:14,155 --> 00:13:15,556
<i>I haven't, but…</i>

187
00:13:17,024 --> 00:13:18,559
<i>Honestly, I'm torn.</i>

188
00:13:20,294 --> 00:13:23,164
But I wanted to talk
to you about it first.

189
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:28,870
Damn it, stay away.

190
00:13:29,837 --> 00:13:32,006
It's too late.

191
00:13:32,073 --> 00:13:35,276
No, we have to keep it secret.

192
00:13:35,977 --> 00:13:37,945
It's finished if he sees her.

193
00:13:38,646 --> 00:13:40,281
His feelings will come back.

194
00:13:41,983 --> 00:13:42,884
You think so?

195
00:13:43,451 --> 00:13:45,853
I told you not to get involved with him.

196
00:13:47,488 --> 00:13:51,959
But it's also not fair
to keep this from him, right?

197
00:13:52,660 --> 00:13:55,897
I mean, he might not think anything of it.

198
00:13:55,963 --> 00:13:59,967
I'm a high school girl now,
we've also hooked up.

199
00:14:00,935 --> 00:14:03,471
You think I'd lose to the memory
of some teacher pushing 30?

200
00:14:03,538 --> 00:14:08,109
I'd be careful, men don't have
to have feelings to handle a girl.

201
00:14:08,175 --> 00:14:10,177
I want to fight on even ground.

202
00:14:10,244 --> 00:14:13,447
Then you tell him.

203
00:14:14,849 --> 00:14:17,785
Do whatever feels right.
You're his girlfriend after all.

204
00:14:22,857 --> 00:14:23,824
I need to go pee.

205
00:14:23,891 --> 00:14:25,726
What is it, Yu?

206
00:14:25,793 --> 00:14:27,795
We had this teacher Ms. Suenaga.

207
00:14:27,862 --> 00:14:30,831
Rumor is that she
messed around with a student.

208
00:14:30,898 --> 00:14:32,833
<i>So they found her.</i>

209
00:14:32,900 --> 00:14:37,171
Okay, we'll be making
the flowers for the recital.

210
00:14:38,005 --> 00:14:41,442
You two, listen to Mr. Nogami!

211
00:14:42,076 --> 00:14:42,944
Hey.

212
00:14:43,010 --> 00:14:45,146
Stop fooling around.

213
00:14:45,212 --> 00:14:46,847
Sit down.

214
00:14:48,015 --> 00:14:51,185
-Take a seat.
-Sit down.

215
00:14:51,252 --> 00:14:54,689
We'll be making flowers like these.

216
00:14:54,755 --> 00:14:56,791
Those are so good, Ms. Hijiri.

217
00:14:56,857 --> 00:14:57,825
-You made them?
-Yes.

218
00:14:57,892 --> 00:15:00,828
Each of you will make three.

219
00:15:01,362 --> 00:15:03,230
-What's that?
-A star fish?

220
00:15:03,297 --> 00:15:04,765
A crushed can?

221
00:15:05,366 --> 00:15:07,735
They're clearly flowers!

222
00:15:09,403 --> 00:15:15,343
Terrible!

223
00:15:15,409 --> 00:15:16,944
All of you sit down.

224
00:15:17,678 --> 00:15:19,380
Okay, I was wrong.

225
00:15:20,481 --> 00:15:21,849
TOKYO

226
00:15:21,916 --> 00:15:25,086
Do you have the report on
the renovation project?

227
00:15:25,586 --> 00:15:26,887
I'm almost done.

228
00:15:36,097 --> 00:15:38,332
Um, so like,

229
00:15:38,833 --> 00:15:44,171
I totally understand girls who need to ask
what their relationship status is.

230
00:15:44,839 --> 00:15:46,007
What?

231
00:15:57,718 --> 00:15:58,886
I'm sorry.

232
00:16:09,730 --> 00:16:10,731
Damn it.

233
00:16:17,838 --> 00:16:20,374
Could you take me out to Roppongi?

234
00:16:20,875 --> 00:16:21,942
W-What?

235
00:16:23,044 --> 00:16:23,878
What?

236
00:16:25,246 --> 00:16:26,180
Where are we going?

237
00:16:27,014 --> 00:16:29,216
I was going to go home and cool down.

238
00:16:30,951 --> 00:16:33,621
The Mongols say
to strike while the iron is hot.

239
00:16:33,688 --> 00:16:35,089
They say that here too.

240
00:16:35,156 --> 00:16:37,258
I don't want my clothes to wrinkle.

241
00:16:38,492 --> 00:16:39,860
So lend me something to wear.

242
00:16:42,697 --> 00:16:43,597
Okay.

243
00:16:44,999 --> 00:16:47,201
-Are you free tonight?
-Why?

244
00:16:47,268 --> 00:16:49,503
I can lend you clothes again.

245
00:16:52,406 --> 00:16:54,442
Your t-shirt was lame.

246
00:16:55,076 --> 00:16:57,611
Sorry, I don't know fashion.

247
00:16:57,678 --> 00:16:59,847
Sometimes your suit is lame too.

248
00:17:00,381 --> 00:17:03,250
Well, I get whatever's on sale.

249
00:17:03,317 --> 00:17:06,253
But I like that about you.

250
00:17:12,626 --> 00:17:13,761
That's good.

251
00:17:16,330 --> 00:17:19,467
-Make sure to add pictures to the report.
-Yes, ma'am.

252
00:17:23,170 --> 00:17:24,772
The digital camera…

253
00:17:33,314 --> 00:17:37,218
<i>I forgot to copy the data</i>
<i>from the camera I returned.</i>

254
00:17:37,284 --> 00:17:39,086
From your boyfriend?

255
00:17:39,754 --> 00:17:41,055
Hello.

256
00:17:41,756 --> 00:17:43,958
Were you out shopping?

257
00:17:46,293 --> 00:17:49,130
Don't worry, I'm cooking for her.

258
00:17:49,764 --> 00:17:51,832
Okay, that's good.

259
00:17:53,300 --> 00:17:54,735
It's so awful.

260
00:17:54,802 --> 00:17:59,707
Small towns like this are always looking
for something to talk about.

261
00:18:00,608 --> 00:18:03,310
I can't even shop in peace.

262
00:18:04,145 --> 00:18:05,546
It's suffocating.

263
00:18:07,548 --> 00:18:08,949
But I hope

264
00:18:11,252 --> 00:18:13,254
I can count on you to be on my side.

265
