got back from the library,

363
00:28:13,783 --> 00:28:15,318
and she got locked out.

364
00:28:15,385 --> 00:28:17,621
Being a teacher sounds tough.

365
00:28:18,922 --> 00:28:19,756
Here.

366
00:28:20,957 --> 00:28:21,858
Right.

367
00:28:24,661 --> 00:28:26,096
Good, it's all here.

368
00:28:27,898 --> 00:28:29,833
I'm saved!

369
00:28:29,900 --> 00:28:31,301
-Thanks.
-No problem.

370
00:28:33,904 --> 00:28:36,973
I just learned that she was here today.
So I rushed here.

371
00:28:38,375 --> 00:28:39,209
Hey, so…

372
00:28:43,246 --> 00:28:44,581
I need to get back to work.

373
00:28:46,516 --> 00:28:47,784
-Thanks.
-Sure.

374
00:28:47,851 --> 00:28:48,919
Later, Hijiri.

375
00:29:08,738 --> 00:29:12,309
Ms. Suenaga,
what a wonderful boyfriend you have.

376
00:29:13,777 --> 00:29:15,445
He seemed very metropolitan.

377
00:29:16,012 --> 00:29:17,681
Why are you keeping him secret?

378
00:29:18,415 --> 00:29:19,950
He's just an old friend.

379
00:29:20,884 --> 00:29:22,185
Anyway, Ayano--

380
00:29:22,252 --> 00:29:25,021
She forgot to take her key with her.

381
00:29:28,625 --> 00:29:31,227
But it's worrying when this
keeps happening.

382
00:29:31,294 --> 00:29:34,064
It's just a misunderstanding, no big deal.

383
00:29:35,932 --> 00:29:39,202
You don't want people talking either,
do you?

384
00:29:43,306 --> 00:29:44,341
Mom.

385
00:29:45,542 --> 00:29:48,111
Ayano, sorry I'm late.

386
00:29:48,178 --> 00:29:51,381
Are you okay? Sorry I was late.

387
00:29:51,448 --> 00:29:52,282
Let's go.

388
00:29:56,886 --> 00:29:58,021
Did you eat?

389
00:29:58,588 --> 00:30:00,156
Want me to cook you something?

390
00:30:05,028 --> 00:30:06,396
TOKYO

391
00:30:07,497 --> 00:30:09,099
I got the pictures right away.

392
00:30:09,733 --> 00:30:10,567
Here you go.

393
00:30:11,201 --> 00:30:13,536
Which means you met Hijiri.

394
00:30:15,071 --> 00:30:16,973
Not just her, but him too.

395
00:30:17,774 --> 00:30:18,908
Him?

396
00:30:22,812 --> 00:30:24,881
So, did you meet her?

397
00:30:27,250 --> 00:30:28,084
Or didn't you?

398
00:30:34,157 --> 00:30:35,158
Then

399
00:30:37,293 --> 00:30:38,762
at least answer this.

400
00:30:39,996 --> 00:30:44,134
Do you like me?

401
00:30:47,637 --> 00:30:48,571
Even just

402
00:30:50,340 --> 00:30:51,174
a little?

403
00:30:55,445 --> 00:30:56,413
Even if it's

404
00:30:58,681 --> 00:30:59,582
past tense?

405
00:31:35,485 --> 00:31:36,352
Runa!

406
00:31:37,754 --> 00:31:38,988
Long time no see!

407
00:31:40,824 --> 00:31:42,525
You're dating Akira?

408
00:31:42,592 --> 00:31:44,994
That's what I heard from
your mother Sayuri.

409
00:31:47,430 --> 00:31:48,364
I had no idea.

410
00:31:51,434 --> 00:31:52,735
It's amazing.

411
00:31:52,802 --> 00:31:53,803
Huh?

412
00:31:55,939 --> 00:32:01,311
When I call him, he would come over.

413
00:32:03,346 --> 00:32:04,848
We'd spend time alone.

414
00:32:06,916 --> 00:32:08,485
He'd be kind to me.

415
00:32:13,623 --> 00:32:18,828
Even if it was just his way
of handling me.

416
00:32:19,462 --> 00:32:20,563
Handling?

417
00:32:21,064 --> 00:32:22,031
What do you mean?

418
00:32:23,633 --> 00:32:24,534
But…

419
00:32:27,403 --> 00:32:28,304
If…

420
00:32:30,440 --> 00:32:32,275
Suenaga steals him again…

421
00:32:32,909 --> 00:32:35,445
You mean that Suenaga?

422
00:32:35,512 --> 00:32:38,748
They haven't met, have they?

423
00:32:42,085 --> 00:32:44,187
That's a bit of a gray area.

424
00:32:44,787 --> 00:32:46,256
-What?
-Gray area?

425
00:32:46,322 --> 00:32:49,826
It seems like he wasn't able to meet her.

426
00:32:51,161 --> 00:32:55,131
But he headed straight for her when
he found out where she was.

427
00:32:56,299 --> 00:32:57,333
In a second.

428
00:33:10,113 --> 00:33:11,347
It's yummy.

429
00:33:11,414 --> 00:33:13,850
If you involve them,
they'll take Ayano from me.

430
00:33:14,817 --> 00:33:18,521
<i>You don't want people talking either,</i>
<i>do you?</i>

431
00:33:44,714 --> 00:33:49,018
So basically,
when the boy showed up to see Hijiri--

432
00:33:49,085 --> 00:33:51,554
He's a young man now, basically an adult.

433
00:33:51,621 --> 00:33:55,225
You acted like you married her
and turned him away.

434
00:33:55,291 --> 00:33:56,926
He just assumed.

435
00:33:56,993 --> 00:33:59,696
And you didn't tell
Hijiri anything on top of that.

436
00:34:00,430 --> 00:34:01,998
I didn't have time.

437
00:34:06,135 --> 00:34:06,970
I'm going home.

438
00:34:07,036 --> 00:34:08,838
What? Why?

439
00:34:09,405 --> 00:34:11,074
Hey, hold on.

440
00:34:12,675 --> 00:34:13,910
What is it?

441
00:34:14,410 --> 00:34:17,113
Since when do you talk to me like that?

442
00:34:18,214 --> 00:34:20,350
Wait, are you jealous?

443
00:34:22,619 --> 00:34:23,453
What?

444
00:34:24,254 --> 00:34:26,889
Because I went to see Hijiri
and turned him away?

445
00:34:28,157 --> 00:34:29,959
You think I'm not over her?

446
00:34:31,661 --> 00:34:32,729
Don't be cocky.

447
00:34:33,296 --> 00:34:34,631
You don't need to worry.

448
00:34:38,334 --> 00:34:40,036
But, it's just…

449
00:34:41,704 --> 00:34:42,538
Just?

450
00:34:45,408 --> 00:34:46,309
What?

451
00:34:48,745 --> 00:34:49,646
In that moment,

452
00:34:51,381 --> 00:34:53,049
the feeling I felt when I saw him

453
00:34:56,152 --> 00:34:57,487
was unforgiving.

454
00:35:01,624 --> 00:35:06,763
If they meet again,
and everyone says that their love is real.

455
00:35:06,829 --> 00:35:08,865
<i>That it's destiny.</i>

456
00:35:11,301 --> 00:35:12,268
I can't forgive it.

457
00:35:17,640 --> 00:35:19,876
Hijiri was wrong.

458
00:35:29,819 --> 00:35:30,687
Kawai.

459
00:35:32,055 --> 00:35:34,857
I don't hate your true thoughts.

460
00:35:36,626 --> 00:35:39,796
Yes, Hijiri was wrong.

461
00:35:41,864 --> 00:35:43,066
But that's how it is.

462
00:35:44,567 --> 00:35:48,805
When you fall for someone,
there's no right or wrong.

463
00:35:49,972 --> 00:35:54,177
It doesn't matter
if it's real or destined either.

464
00:35:55,378 --> 00:35:56,646
You just love them.

465
00:35:58,548 --> 00:36:00,316
<i>It's hopeless attraction.</i>

466
00:36:01,184 --> 00:36:02,285
<i>That's love.</i>

467
00:36:09,459 --> 00:36:11,761
<i>Poor Hijiri.</i>

468
00:36:12,662 --> 00:36:16,666
<i>All alone in an unfamiliar city,</i>
<i>not even knowing he came.</i>

469
00:36:17,400 --> 00:36:22,271
Imagining how hard she's working,
I feel bad for her.

470
00:36:24,374 --> 00:36:25,541
Makes me want to

471
00:36:27,076 --> 00:36:28,311
go give her a hug.

472
00:36:29,612 --> 00:36:30,713
What?

473
00:36:32,849 --> 00:36:34,117
That's how I am.

474
00:36:36,919 --> 00:36:42,392
Kawai, the way things are going,
do you see us working out?

475
00:37:08,317 --> 00:37:09,185
Akira.

476
00:37:16,526 --> 00:37:17,360
Welcome home.

477
00:37:22,999 --> 00:37:24,901
Wait, Akira!

478
00:37:25,535 --> 00:37:26,369
Hey!

479
00:37:31,707 --> 00:37:33,776
It's late, why don't you stay the night.

480
00:37:38,681 --> 00:37:40,550
You saw your room, didn't you?

481
00:37:41,951 --> 00:37:43,686
I left it the way it was.

482
00:37:44,587 --> 00:37:46,456
You can come home whenever you want.

483
00:37:49,492 --> 00:37:53,563
This is your home after all.

