500
00:39:53,282 --> 00:39:54,650
Hello!

501
00:39:55,551 --> 00:39:56,819
Bye!

502
00:39:56,886 --> 00:39:58,621
Good bye, don't run.

503
00:40:02,425 --> 00:40:03,659
Goodbye.

504
00:40:06,562 --> 00:40:07,930
Good work today.

505
00:40:13,569 --> 00:40:15,504
Why did you call them!

506
00:40:15,571 --> 00:40:17,273
-What?
-I told you not to!

507
00:40:17,340 --> 00:40:20,309
-Why Ayano!
-Did something happen to her?

508
00:40:20,376 --> 00:40:21,477
They took her away!

509
00:40:21,544 --> 00:40:25,715
My parents sent a car and took Ayano away!

510
00:40:25,781 --> 00:40:26,849
Calm down!

511
00:40:26,916 --> 00:40:29,118
-What's this commotion?
-Please stop!

512
00:40:29,185 --> 00:40:31,187
You're all liars!

513
00:40:31,253 --> 00:40:34,857
Pretending to be on my side,
but you were lying!

514
00:40:34,924 --> 00:40:36,726
We're all on your side!

515
00:40:36,792 --> 00:40:39,261
I know about it.

516
00:40:57,534 --> 00:40:58,401
Ms. Tachibana?

517
00:40:59,202 --> 00:41:03,773
Ms. Suenaga, you and Mr. Nogami
are an item, aren't you?

518
00:41:03,840 --> 00:41:05,142
What?

519
00:41:05,208 --> 00:41:08,111
I saw you two eating together.

520
00:41:08,178 --> 00:41:11,882
-You even went to the next town over.
-It's a misunderstanding.

521
00:41:11,948 --> 00:41:14,918
And what was that yesterday, an affair?

522
00:41:15,452 --> 00:41:17,320
Bringing over that businessman.

523
00:41:17,821 --> 00:41:20,957
No, he's an old friend.

524
00:41:21,024 --> 00:41:23,260
You're no different.

525
00:41:23,326 --> 00:41:26,763
Your girlfriend's two-timing you
and acting all superior.

526
00:41:26,830 --> 00:41:27,731
We're not!

527
00:41:27,797 --> 00:41:29,132
You're being tricked!

528
00:41:29,199 --> 00:41:30,233
No!

529
00:41:30,934 --> 00:41:35,005
This is just a one-sided crush on my end.

530
00:41:36,907 --> 00:41:38,074
What?

531
00:41:38,141 --> 00:41:39,342
What'd you say?

532
00:41:39,409 --> 00:41:41,111
Oh, no, really?

533
00:41:43,813 --> 00:41:46,449
We haven't done anything inappropriate.

534
00:41:47,884 --> 00:41:49,786
And Ms. Suenaga didn't know.

535
00:41:51,221 --> 00:41:54,224
I'm the one who called your parents.

536
00:41:56,459 --> 00:41:59,996
I called them when I heard Ayano
was locked out.

537
00:42:00,063 --> 00:42:01,631
<i>They said they'd take her.</i>

538
00:42:02,933 --> 00:42:05,068
Grandma, Nana fetched!

539
00:42:07,904 --> 00:42:12,375
-I told you not to contact them.
-And I warned you too!

540
00:42:12,442 --> 00:42:18,615
If you neglected Ayano's care again,
that I would call your parents.

541
00:42:20,083 --> 00:42:22,686
I never neglected her!

542
00:42:22,752 --> 00:42:24,387
You put her in danger!

543
00:42:27,724 --> 00:42:31,294
We can always talk about
how we can move forward.

544
00:42:33,597 --> 00:42:35,065
Call me any time.

545
00:42:42,973 --> 00:42:44,140
Unforgivable.

546
00:42:45,275 --> 00:42:48,478
If Ayano never comes home again,

547
00:42:50,580 --> 00:42:52,148
I'll never forgive you!

548
00:42:56,319 --> 00:42:58,121
What is her problem?

549
00:42:58,188 --> 00:43:00,056
What a hypocrite.

550
00:43:00,123 --> 00:43:02,592
I'm glad he made that call before
something happened.

551
00:43:02,659 --> 00:43:04,628
-Yes.
-Absolutely.

552
00:43:04,694 --> 00:43:06,930
Ayano is often left home alone at night.

553
00:43:06,997 --> 00:43:08,965
It's our job to protect children.

554
00:43:09,032 --> 00:43:12,569
-That's right.
-Maybe I should go talk to her again.

555
00:43:14,571 --> 00:43:15,905
More importantly,

556
00:43:17,240 --> 00:43:20,577
has she been harassing you like that
for a while now?

557
00:43:23,413 --> 00:43:24,247
Yes.

558
00:43:26,950 --> 00:43:30,387
I'm sure you don't want to be
the target of any rumor,

559
00:43:30,954 --> 00:43:33,390
but we need to be firm
with parents like her.

560
00:43:34,691 --> 00:43:36,092
Please talk to me next time.

561
00:43:39,362 --> 00:43:41,898
Understood. I'm sorry.

562
00:43:43,633 --> 00:43:44,834
Good.

563
00:43:46,503 --> 00:43:49,172
Can you believe the two of them?

564
00:43:49,239 --> 00:43:51,641
What's going to happen now?

565
00:44:05,121 --> 00:44:06,356
I'm sorry about that.

566
00:44:08,425 --> 00:44:09,292
But

567
00:44:11,328 --> 00:44:12,562
that's how I feel.

568
00:44:15,098 --> 00:44:16,333
I do hope

569
00:44:18,435 --> 00:44:20,337
to date you someday.

570
00:44:23,540 --> 00:44:26,676
I know you don't think of me that way yet.

571
00:44:28,912 --> 00:44:31,915
But maybe

572
00:44:33,249 --> 00:44:36,286
we could slowly build something

573
00:44:39,956 --> 00:44:43,059
so someday you might have feelings for me.

574
00:44:47,130 --> 00:44:48,832
I don't need an answer right away.

575
00:44:50,767 --> 00:44:54,771
Just think about it.

576
00:44:57,574 --> 00:44:58,408
Okay.

577
00:45:01,911 --> 00:45:03,146
We just got word.

578
00:45:04,214 --> 00:45:06,950
-Ayano is missing.
-What?

579
00:45:14,389 --> 00:45:16,190
-Excuse me.
-Yes?

580
00:45:17,225 --> 00:45:20,328
-Have you seen Ayano Tachibana?
-No, I haven't seen Ayano.

581
00:45:20,962 --> 00:45:22,163
You haven't?

582
00:45:22,830 --> 00:45:23,965
Tachibana!

583
00:45:25,099 --> 00:45:26,200
Tachibana!

584
00:45:28,035 --> 00:45:30,938
A neighbor saw her leaving alone.

585
00:45:31,606 --> 00:45:33,908
-Maybe she's trying to go home.
-Yes.

586
00:45:34,575 --> 00:45:37,445
Damn, I can't get a hold of her mother.

587
00:45:45,253 --> 00:45:46,354
Tachibana.

588
00:45:47,989 --> 00:45:48,923
Tachibana?

589
00:45:49,490 --> 00:45:50,825
Excuse me!

590
00:45:51,826 --> 00:45:53,961
Have you seen a little girl around here?

591
00:45:54,695 --> 00:45:55,930
Tachibana!

592
00:45:59,567 --> 00:46:00,768
Tachibana!

593
00:46:02,570 --> 00:46:03,838
Tachibana.

594
00:46:07,442 --> 00:46:08,509
Tachibana!

595
00:46:11,412 --> 00:46:12,480
Are you okay?

596
00:46:14,315 --> 00:46:17,185
Thank goodness, we were worried.

597
00:46:21,489 --> 00:46:22,890
Were you going home?

598
00:46:24,659 --> 00:46:25,827
Your mom wasn't home?

599
00:46:28,729 --> 00:46:31,699
I tried to go back to Grandma's,

600
00:46:33,000 --> 00:46:35,303
but I got lost.

601
00:46:36,904 --> 00:46:38,773
Then this big brother helped me.

602
00:47:12,206 --> 00:47:13,441
Ms. Suenaga!

603
00:47:15,409 --> 00:47:17,645
Thank goodness you found her.

604
00:47:26,320 --> 00:47:27,688
Let's go, Tachibana.

605
00:47:28,823 --> 00:47:29,657
Wait!

606
00:47:30,858 --> 00:47:32,026
I can take her.

607
00:47:32,860 --> 00:47:33,694
What?

608
00:47:37,798 --> 00:47:41,269
I'll be waiting at the school.

609
00:47:51,746 --> 00:47:52,580
Ready?

610
00:47:55,917 --> 00:47:56,851
Let's go.

611
00:47:57,919 --> 00:47:58,753
Later.

612
00:48:20,207 --> 00:48:21,042
What?

613
00:48:21,609 --> 00:48:24,345
Wait, no way, yuck! Hey!

614
00:48:24,946 --> 00:48:27,214
Is it a stink bug?
It's a stink bug, right?

615
00:48:28,015 --> 00:48:28,916
No.

616
00:48:45,132 --> 00:48:46,067
Stinks.

617
00:48:50,404 --> 00:48:51,672
Kuroiwa.

618
00:48:54,742 --> 00:48:56,210
Why are you here?

619
00:48:58,879 --> 00:49:01,749
Well, what are you doing here?

620
00:49:04,418 --> 00:49:08,322
That little girl said you weren't married.

621
00:49:12,093 --> 00:49:15,796
I thought you got married
to that Shotaro guy

622
00:49:16,364 --> 00:49:19,200
and were buying IKEA furniture together.

623
00:49:20,901 --> 00:49:25,706
Maybe you'd already have a kid,
and became a housewife or something.

624
00:49:27,508 --> 00:49:31,078
So why are you still teaching?

625
00:49:33,781 --> 00:49:35,583
You came this far to ask me that?

626
00:49:37,385 --> 00:49:38,586
No, I didn't.

627
00:49:39,086 --> 00:49:41,756
I'm dating Iwasaki now.

628
00:49:46,193 --> 00:49:48,162
She has a good head on her shoulders.

629
00:49:48,896 --> 00:49:49,997
Not to say you don't--

630
00:49:50,064 --> 00:49:51,132
Can I…

631
00:49:52,400 --> 00:49:54,201
Can I come here again?

632
00:49:55,936 --> 00:49:56,771
What?

633
00:49:56,837 --> 00:49:59,640
You're not with that
Shotaro guy anymore, right?

634
00:50:01,676 --> 00:50:04,045
And you're not my teacher anymore, right?

635
00:50:09,150 --> 00:50:11,552
I'm 18 now.

636
00:50:18,325 --> 00:50:19,860
I will break up with Iwasaki.

637
00:50:22,296 --> 00:50:25,166
There's no reason
I can't come see you, right?

638
00:50:28,869 --> 00:50:30,037
Now I'm…

639
00:50:34,842 --> 00:50:35,910
I'm still…

640
00:50:39,113 --> 00:50:40,781
the same as on that day.

641
00:50:43,818 --> 00:50:47,722
Back on that beach
after the fireworks festival,

642
00:50:50,391 --> 00:50:51,225
still…

643
00:50:52,993 --> 00:50:56,464
No matter who is against it,

644
00:50:59,300 --> 00:51:00,835
I will come see you.

645
00:51:09,744 --> 00:51:10,578
I will always--

646
00:51:16,150 --> 00:51:17,351
Never come again.

647
00:51:18,085 --> 00:51:19,820
If you come here,

648
00:51:21,589 --> 00:51:23,124
I'll have to move away.

649
00:51:34,268 --> 00:51:35,302
I have

650
00:51:37,872 --> 00:51:39,640
students I care about here.

651
00:51:42,543 --> 00:51:43,811
I can't lose them.

652
00:51:49,049 --> 00:51:50,151
Never come again.

653
00:51:59,527 --> 00:52:01,662
You'll miss your last train.

654
00:52:02,396 --> 00:52:03,464
You'll be stuck here.

655
00:52:07,401 --> 00:52:08,803
You can borrow my bike.

656
00:52:09,904 --> 00:52:11,872
Just park it in front of the station.

657
00:52:12,807 --> 00:52:13,774
Here.

658
00:52:31,692 --> 00:52:32,526
Thanks.

659
00:54:04,885 --> 00:54:07,688
HIJIRI, I WANT TO SEE YOU.

660
00:54:07,755 --> 00:54:10,190
I WANT TO SEE YOU. KUROIWA.

661
00:54:46,226 --> 00:54:47,594
Ms. Suenaga!

662
00:54:48,329 --> 00:54:50,364
What're you doing here?

663
00:54:56,103 --> 00:54:58,238
-Mr. Nogami.
-Yes?

664
00:55:01,508 --> 00:55:05,079
Can I give you my answer now?

665
00:55:06,413 --> 00:55:07,448
Of course.

666
00:55:08,215 --> 00:55:09,116
Hold on.

667
00:55:10,017 --> 00:55:10,884
Okay.

668
00:55:14,321 --> 00:55:18,359
If you would have me,
maybe we could get to know each other

669
00:55:21,528 --> 00:55:22,963
a little bit at a time.

670
00:55:24,999 --> 00:55:25,866
Yes!

671
00:55:27,067 --> 00:55:29,603
I would be honored!

672
00:55:45,219 --> 00:55:46,053
Sorry.

673
00:55:46,120 --> 00:55:47,087
Sorry.

674
00:55:47,988 --> 00:55:49,390
Crap, we need to hurry!

675
00:55:50,457 --> 00:55:51,392
You're right!

676
00:56:12,479 --> 00:56:13,380
Why?

677
00:56:30,164 --> 00:56:33,667
You messed around with your middle school
student three years ago?

678
00:56:33,734 --> 00:56:35,469
I'm disappointed.

679
00:56:35,536 --> 00:56:37,104
I can't become a good teacher.

680
00:56:37,171 --> 00:56:39,640
Would you leave this town with me?

681
00:56:39,706 --> 00:56:41,141
Subtitle translation by: Zensho Yamamoto

